<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Space Management on Saitech</title><link>https://saitech.blog/tags/space-management/</link><description>Recent content in Space Management on Saitech</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Tue, 21 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://saitech.blog/tags/space-management/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Quick Tools to Manage Space Usage</title><link>https://saitech.blog/p/quick-tools-to-manage-space-usage/</link><pubDate>Tue, 21 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://saitech.blog/p/quick-tools-to-manage-space-usage/</guid><description>&lt;img src="https://saitech.blog/p/quick-tools-to-manage-space-usage/1.png" alt="Featured image of post Quick Tools to Manage Space Usage" />&lt;p>From time to time, you might need to free up disk space, but where do you start? How can you quickly locate those large files taking up valuable storage? Letâ€™s explore some options. Spoiler alert: The first two are my top picks!&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="terminal">Terminal
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>Command to Locate Large Files&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">find / -type f -size +2000M 2&amp;gt;/dev/null
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>&lt;code>/&lt;/code>: Search from the root directory (change to specific directories like /home or /var for faster results).&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;code>-type f&lt;/code>: Search for files only.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;code>-size +2000M&lt;/code>: Files larger than 2000 MB.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;code>2&amp;gt;/dev/null&lt;/code>: Suppress permission denied errors.&lt;/p>
